{
  "texts": [
    "The maximum unvoiced duration and the voice probability threshold alternatively rely on one another to determine when to segment the speech input prior to reaching the maximum segment duration.",
    "The first part of this second facet of segmentation begins with the Silero VAD model (Team, 2024).",
    "This VAD model outputs a probability score of a specific sample containing audio of a speaker's voice.",
    "If the score falls below the voice probability threshold, it is determined that there is currently no voice from the speaker.",
    "When the score has been below the probability threshold for longer than the maximum unvoiced duration, the speech is segmented."
  ]
}